**Segments**

- Based on drug class, the endocarditis drug market can be segmented into antibiotics and combination therapy. Antibiotics are the most commonly prescribed drugs for treating endocarditis due to their ability to target and kill the bacteria causing the infection. Combination therapy, on the other hand, involves using a combination of different antibiotics to enhance efficacy and reduce the risk of antibiotic resistance.

- On the basis of distribution channel, the market can be categorized into hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies. Hospital pharmacies play a crucial role in dispensing drugs for inpatient treatment of endocarditis, while retail and online pharmacies serve as important channels for providing medications to patients for outpatient management and maintenance therapy.

- Geographically, the endocarditis drug market can be divided into North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, Latin America, and Middle East & Africa. North America is expected to dominate the market due to the high prevalence of endocarditis cases, well-established healthcare infrastructure, and strong R&D activities. Europe is also anticipated to show significant growth, driven by increasing awareness about the disease and advancements in treatment options.

